.TH "ftrace_set_filter" 9 "ftrace_set_filter" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ftrace_set_filter \- set a function to filter on in ftrace @ops - the ops to set the filter with @buf - the string that holds the function filter text. @len - the length of the string. @reset - non zero to reset all filters before applying this filter.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ftrace_set_filter
.BI "(struct ftrace_ops *ops "  ","
.BI "unsigned char *buf "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "int reset "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ops" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "buf" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "len" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "reset" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Filters denote which functions should be enabled when tracing is enabled.
If \fIbuf\fP is NULL and reset is set, all functions will be enabled for tracing.
